name: empty beach
description: I want to hear the sand, grain by grain, folding over itself in the wind. I want to hear the pulse of the waves, and the whisper of whatever lies across them. An experience is layers of texture and nuanced perception, down to the perfume of redwood and salty air, that, even a hint, can bring me right back to this spot. ||| shot on Canon AE-1 and Portra 400 film
